WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.404 --> 00:00:02.944
Warehousing is the physical management of items

2
00:00:02.944 --> 00:00:04.555
within an organization.

3
00:00:04.555 --> 00:00:08.043
It includes the physical receipt of incoming items,

4
00:00:08.043 --> 00:00:11.102
the physical storage and control of items.

5
00:00:11.102 --> 00:00:15.368
Picking, packing, and staging against orders and shipping.

6
00:00:15.368 --> 00:00:18.066
Physical receipt involves accepting items

7
00:00:18.066 --> 00:00:22.093
into the organization, unloading them from inbound carriers,

8
00:00:22.093 --> 00:00:24.247
and verifying correct quantities,

9
00:00:24.247 --> 00:00:26.488
qualities, and documentation.

10
00:00:26.488 --> 00:00:29.235
Storage and control of items involves

11
00:00:29.235 --> 00:00:31.710
moving accepted items into the warehouse,

12
00:00:31.710 --> 00:00:34.149
putting them away into correct locations,

13
00:00:34.149 --> 00:00:37.760
recording locations and amounts into an inventory system,

14
00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:39.853
verifying locations and amounts

15
00:00:39.853 --> 00:00:42.174
against inventory system records,

16
00:00:42.174 --> 00:00:45.257
and controlling physical access to the items.

17
00:00:45.257 --> 00:00:48.610
Picking, packing and staging involves physically

18
00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:51.135
selecting the correct items and amounts

19
00:00:51.135 --> 00:00:52.884
ordered from the warehouse.

20
00:00:52.884 --> 00:00:55.180
Decrementing the inventory records,

21
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:58.220
placing the items into appropriate containers,

22
00:00:58.220 --> 00:01:00.599
labeling the containers as required,

23
00:01:00.599 --> 00:01:02.832
and moving the containers to an area

24
00:01:02.832 --> 00:01:04.816
to building shipping loads.

25
00:01:04.816 --> 00:01:07.770
Shipping involves loading outbound carriers

26
00:01:07.770 --> 00:01:10.411
with packed orders and completing and providing

27
00:01:10.411 --> 00:01:14.063
associated documentation, such as bills of lading.

28
00:01:14.063 --> 00:01:17.067
An example of warehousing an industry would include

29
00:01:17.067 --> 00:01:19.000
storing items for Walmart.

30
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.401
For instance, Walmart has distribution centers that

31
00:01:22.401 --> 00:01:26.267
will store items until requested by the stores to stock.

